    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWith `set mouse=` and `set mousescroll=ver:0`, vertical scrolling with the mouse will still be enabled. I think this is because `mouse_on/mouse_off` UI events are not emitted when `mouse` is empty.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- `nvim --clean somescrollablebuffer.txt`\n- `:set mouse= mousescroll=ver:0`\n- Scroll in the buffer\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nVertical scrolling should be disabled, since `mousescroll=ver:0`\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-nightly+e21c540 (commit bf1d4e9793fcad74085ff6c32a6da5c43fe891e3)\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNA\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nNixOS 25.11 (Xantusia) x86_64\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.1.3\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nnixos nightly overlay",
